			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, I'm currently a level 48 Druid, but I've been soloing these bloody bastards for 13 levels now, and I hope this info will help Druids that are new to Rathe and who want to get on the fast track to mega-pp and richs. First, get your WIS up as high as possible before trying this, you will need all your mana at levels 35 to 39 to solo a blue HG. The best level to try and start doing this is at 35th. Try to get a Clarity until level 39. Be in wolf form and locate a blue HG, pull with snare (if it does not stick, kite and keep trying), and kite the HG to a secluded part of the HG valley for liquidation. Cast Drones of Doom on the HG as it approaches you, then root it, and then get Immolate to stick on it. At level 39 use Ro's Fiery Sundering to lower the HG's fire resistance so you can get Immolate to stick on it easier. After you have snare, root and the two dots on the HG, sit and med till root breaks. Then re-apply root, and med once more. Repeat this overall process till the HG is meat, and don't forget to re-apply snare after about the 2nd set of dots (Drones of Doom and Immolate). I discovered from experience that it take about 4 sets of Drones of Doom and Immolate to whack the HG. At level 44 it takes 3 Drifting Death spells and 2 Immolates to drop the HG, generally speaking. The important thing is to use the downtime when the HG is rooted to med some. Then repeat this dance till the HG is pp in your pocket.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck!<BR>
<BR>
Heydrich, 48th Druid<BR>
7th Hammer
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
